
@startuml

' Define classes
class Contract {
    +String id
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate
    +String termsAndConditions
}

class Acquisition {
    +String acquisitionId
    +int quantity
    +Date deliveryDate
    +double negotiatedPrice
    +String customizations
    +String model
}

class AirlineCompany {
    +String name
    +String country
    +String contactInfo
}

class Salesperson {
    +String employeeId
    +String name
    +String email
}

class AircraftModel {
    +String modelNumber
    +String description
}

class Relationship {
    +String relationshipType  // e.g., "Mother-Daughter"
    +AirlineCompany parent
    +AirlineCompany child
}

' Associations
Contract "1" *-- "many" Acquisition : contains
Contract "1" --> "1..*" Salesperson : managedBy
Acquisition "1" --> "1" AircraftModel : uses
Acquisition "1" --> "1" AirlineCompany : soldTo
AirlineCompany "0..*" -- "0..*" AirlineCompany : relatedVia <.. Relationship

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Contract`**: Represents a global agreement between Boeing and an airline company. It may include multiple `Acquisition`s.
- **`Acquisition`**: Represents the purchase of one or more aircrafts under a contract. Each has specific details like model, price, and delivery date.
- **`AircraftModel`**: Describes the type/model of the aircraft being acquired.
- **`Salesperson`**: Manages contracts. One salesperson can manage many contracts.
- **`AirlineCompany`**: The customer (airline) buying aircrafts. They can be part of a mother-daughter relationship.
- **`Relationship`**: Tracks relationships between airline companies (e.g., mother-daughter).

